{"cursor":"43047","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox company\n| company_name = Bigelow Aerospace company_logo = company_type = Private\n| foundation = 1999 founder =\n| Robert Bigelow (Founder and President) location_city = North Las Vegas, Nevada\n| location_country = United States key_people = industry = Aerospace products =\n| Orbital facilities, commercial space stations revenue = operating_income =\n| net_income = num_employees = 50 (October 2011) company_slogan = Join the Adventure! homepage =\n| [http://www.bigelowaerospace.com BigelowAerospace.com] footnotes =\n}}\n\n'Bigelow Aerospace' is a North Las Vegas, Nevada space technology startup\ncompany that is pioneering work on expandable space station modules. Bigelow\nAerospace was founded by Robert Bigelow in 1998 [http://www.spaceflightnow.com/news/n0409/27bigelow/ Bigelow's\nGamble] [[Aviation Week & Space Technology]], 2004-09-26, reprint (authorized),\nRetrieved February 17, 2010. and is funded in large part by the fortune\nBigelow gained through his ownership of the hotel chain Budget Suites of\nAmerica. By 2010, Bigelow had invested US$180 million in the company. [http://www.economist.com/science-\ntechnology/displaystory.cfm?story_id=15543675 The Americans may still go to the\nmoon before the Chinese], [[The Economist]], 2010-02-18, Retrieved March 4,\n2010. Bigelow has stated on multiple occasions that he is prepared to fund\nBigelow Aerospace with about US$500 million through 2015 in order to achieve\nlaunch of full-scale hardware. [http://www.airspacemag.com/space-\nexploration/16047742.html Mr. B's Big Plan], Geoffrey Little, [[Air &\nSpace/Smithsonian|Air & Space Magazine]], 2008-01-01, Retrieved February 18,\n2010 Bigelow is pioneering a new market in a flexible and configurable set\nof space . Moreover, industry\nobservers have noted that Bigelow is demonstrating audacity to pioneer such a\nmarket \"in a capital-intensive, highly-regulated industry like spaceflight.\